NEXOTFE ERP Industrial

==========================================================
PURPOSE
==========================================================

This document defines the official Supabase engineering standards for the NEXOTFE ERP.

Every database decision must comply with these standards.

Consistency is mandatory.

==========================================================
SUPABASE PHILOSOPHY
==========================================================

Supabase is the official Backend-as-a-Service platform for NEXOTFE.

PostgreSQL is the official database.

Every database structure must represent real business entities.

The database is the foundation of the ERP.

Frontend and Backend are built on top of it.

==========================================================
DATABASE PRINCIPLES
==========================================================

The database represents the business.

Never create tables to represent screens.

Never create fields to satisfy temporary interface needs.

Every table must exist because a business entity exists.

==========================================================
PRIMARY KEYS
==========================================================

Every table must use:

UUID

Primary Key

Generated automatically.

Sequential numeric IDs must never be used as primary keys.

==========================================================
AUDIT FIELDS
==========================================================

Every master and transactional table must contain:

id

created_at

updated_at

created_by

empresa_id

Whenever applicable:

deleted_at

deleted_by

These fields are mandatory standards.

==========================================================
MULTI-COMPANY
==========================================================

NEXOTFE is a multi-company ERP.

Every business table must belong to one company.

Use:

empresa_id

Never mix information from different companies.

==========================================================
SOFT DELETE
==========================================================

Business data must never be physically deleted.

Use logical deletion whenever possible.

Official fields:

ativo

deleted_at

deleted_by

Physical DELETE is exceptional.

==========================================================
ROW LEVEL SECURITY
==========================================================

RLS is mandatory.

Every business table must protect company data.

Users must access only authorized information.

Security is mandatory.

Convenience is never a justification for disabling RLS.

==========================================================
FOREIGN KEYS
==========================================================

Relationships must exist only when required by business rules.

Never create unnecessary relationships.

Never relate tables because they "look related".

Relationships represent real business processes.

==========================================================
INDEXES
==========================================================

Indexes must improve performance.

Never create unnecessary indexes.

Typical indexed fields:

empresa_id

created_at

updated_at

ativo

Business search fields

Indexes must be reviewed periodically.

==========================================================
NAMING STANDARD
==========================================================

Use consistent naming.

Examples:

cliente_id

fornecedor_id

produto_id

recurso_id

empresa_id

created_at

updated_at

deleted_at

Never mix languages.

Never use abbreviations unless officially approved.

==========================================================
DATA TYPES
==========================================================

Choose data types according to business meaning.

Do not oversize fields.

Avoid generic text fields when a specific type exists.

==========================================================
MIGRATIONS
==========================================================

Every structural modification must be executed through migrations.

Never modify Production manually.

Every migration must be reversible whenever possible.

==========================================================
DATABASE CHANGES
==========================================================

Before changing any table:

Understand the business rule.

Verify impacts.

Check related modules.

Protect existing data.

Only then implement.

==========================================================
PERFORMANCE
==========================================================

Performance must be considered from the beginning.

Avoid unnecessary joins.

Avoid duplicated data.

Prefer normalized structures.

Denormalization only when technically justified.

==========================================================
BUSINESS CONSISTENCY
==========================================================

Business consistency is more important than programming convenience.

Never simplify the business to simplify the code.

Simplify the code.

Never simplify the business.

==========================================================
IMPLEMENTATION ORDER
==========================================================

Review.

Approve.

Implement.

Test.

Freeze.

Proceed to the next module.

Never skip steps.

==========================================================
ERROR PREVENTION
==========================================================

Before implementing any modification ask internally:

Does this represent the business?

Will this preserve data integrity?

Will this affect other modules?

Can this be maintained in five years?

If any answer is uncertain,

stop and ask.

==========================================================
FINAL PRINCIPLE
==========================================================

Supabase is not simply a database.

It is the digital representation of an industrial company.

Every table,

every field,

every relationship,

must exist because a real business process exists.

Nothing else.